00:37:07.040 --> 00:37:10.325
And voila, safer meat.

00:37:12.784 --> 00:37:13.700
We did kidney failure.

00:37:13.700 --> 00:37:15.480
What about liver failure?

00:37:15.480 --> 00:37:18.750
We've known for decades
that a plant-based diet can

00:37:18.750 --> 00:37:21.734
be used to treat liver
failure, significantly reducing

00:37:21.734 --> 00:37:23.900
the toxins that would
otherwise build up eating meat

00:37:23.900 --> 00:37:26.640
without a fully functional liver
just to detoxify your blood.

00:37:26.640 --> 00:37:28.410
One does have to admit,
though, that there

00:37:28.410 --> 00:37:30.150
are some people eating
plant-based diets

00:37:30.150 --> 00:37:33.350
with worsening liver function.

00:37:33.350 --> 00:37:36.350
They're called
alcoholics, living off

00:37:36.350 --> 00:37:39.080
of potatoes, and corn,
and grapes, and barley.

00:37:39.080 --> 00:37:40.410
In fact, strictly plant-based.

00:37:40.410 --> 00:37:41.870
But they're not doing so well.

00:37:41.870 --> 00:37:44.250
It's not clear what the--

00:37:44.250 --> 00:37:47.560
High blood pressure
is next, affecting

00:37:47.560 --> 00:37:49.230
nearly 78 million Americans.

00:37:49.230 --> 00:37:50.385
That's one in three of us.

00:37:50.385 --> 00:37:52.510
And as we age, our pressures
get higher and higher.

00:37:52.510 --> 00:37:57.492
Such that by age 60, it
strikes more than half.

00:37:57.492 --> 00:37:58.200
So wait a second.

00:37:58.200 --> 00:38:00.130
If it effects most of
us when we get older,

00:38:00.130 --> 00:38:02.360
maybe it's less a
disease and really just

00:38:02.360 --> 00:38:06.770
kind of an inevitable
consequence of aging?

00:38:06.770 --> 00:38:07.270
No.

00:38:07.270 --> 00:38:10.610
We've known since the 1920s that
high blood pressure need not

00:38:10.610 --> 00:38:11.190
occur.

00:38:11.190 --> 00:38:12.530
Researchers measured
the blood pressure

00:38:12.530 --> 00:38:14.030
of a thousand people
in rural Kenya,

00:38:14.030 --> 00:38:16.740
who ate a diet centered around
whole plant foods, whole

00:38:16.740 --> 00:38:18.270
grains, beans,
vegetables, fruit,

00:38:18.270 --> 00:38:19.480
dark-green leafy vegetables.

00:38:19.480 --> 00:38:23.240
Our pressures go up as we age.

00:38:23.240 --> 00:38:28.140
And their pressures actually
get better as they get older.

00:38:28.140 --> 00:38:29.600
And the lower, the better.

00:38:29.600 --> 00:38:32.970
This whole 140 over 90
cutoff is arbitrary.

00:38:32.970 --> 00:38:34.710
Even people who start
out with a blood

00:38:34.710 --> 00:38:37.090
pressure of so-called
normal, 120 over 80,

00:38:37.090 --> 00:38:40.150
appear to benefit from
blood pressure reduction.

00:38:40.150 --> 00:38:43.930
So the ideal blood pressure,
the no-benefit from reducing it

00:38:43.930 --> 00:38:49.310
further blood pressure,
is actually 110 over 70.

00:38:49.310 --> 00:38:52.560
Isn't it even possible to get
pressures down to 110 over 70?

00:38:52.560 --> 00:38:56.830
It's not just possible,
it's normal for people

00:38:56.830 --> 00:38:59.240
eating healthy enough diets.

00:38:59.240 --> 00:39:02.000
So for two years at a rural
Kenyan hospital, 1,800 patients

00:39:02.000 --> 00:39:05.510
admitted, how many cases of high
blood pressure did they find?

00:39:05.510 --> 00:39:06.066
Zero.

00:39:06.066 --> 00:39:08.440
Ah, they must have had low
rates of heart disease, right?

00:39:08.440 --> 00:39:08.940
No.

00:39:08.940 --> 00:39:10.910
They had no rates
of heart disease,

00:39:10.910 --> 00:39:13.900
not a single case
of atherosclerosis,

00:39:13.900 --> 00:39:17.210
arteriosclerosis, our number
one killer, was found.

00:39:17.210 --> 00:39:22.010
Rural China too, by 110
over 70 their entire lives.

00:39:22.010 --> 00:39:26.150
70-year-old, same blood
pressure as a 16-year-old.

00:39:26.150 --> 00:39:29.180
Now, look, Africa, China,
vastly different diets.

00:39:29.180 --> 00:39:31.000
But what do they hold in common?

00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:33.200
The common theme, they're
plant-based day to day,

00:39:33.200 --> 00:39:35.790
with meat only eaten
on special occasions.

00:39:35.790 --> 00:39:38.120
Now, why do we think it's
the plant-based nature

00:39:38.120 --> 00:39:39.920
of their diets though?

00:39:39.920 --> 00:39:44.040
Because in the Western world, as
the American Heart Association

00:39:44.040 --> 00:39:47.260
pointed out, the only folks that
are getting it down that low

00:39:47.260 --> 00:39:53.669
are the strict vegetarians,
coming in at 110 over 65.

00:39:53.669 --> 00:39:56.210
Based on the largest study of
those eating a plant-based diet

00:39:56.210 --> 00:39:58.840
to date, that is
89,000 Californians,

00:39:58.840 --> 00:40:02.020
there appears to be a stepwise
drop in high blood pressure

00:40:02.020 --> 00:40:04.370
rates as one gets more
and more plant-based.

00:40:04.370 --> 00:40:09.110
So this is starting out
a regular meat eater.

00:40:09.110 --> 00:40:13.363
The control group actually
only ate serving or two

00:40:13.363 --> 00:40:13.980
of meat a day.

00:40:13.980 --> 00:40:15.730
So kind of a low meat eater.

00:40:15.730 --> 00:40:17.900
Compared to a semi-vegetarian
or a flexitarian,

00:40:17.900 --> 00:40:19.830
who only meat like
on a weekly basis,

00:40:19.830 --> 00:40:21.280
as opposed to a daily basis.

00:40:21.280 --> 00:40:22.961
Those that ate no
meat except fish,

00:40:22.961 --> 00:40:25.460
just eggs and dairy, or those
that ate strictly plant-based.

00:40:25.460 --> 00:40:28.640
You see the same thing with
diabetes, a stepwise drop

00:40:28.640 --> 00:40:31.700
in diabetes rates as one's diet
gets more and more plant-based.

00:40:31.700 --> 00:40:34.660
And the same thing with obesity,
anything over 25 is overweight.

00:40:34.660 --> 00:40:36.980
Even vegetarians in
the US are overweight.

00:40:36.980 --> 00:40:39.800
The only dietary group that
met the, quote, unquote,

00:40:39.800 --> 00:40:42.660
"ideal body weight" were those
eating strictly plant-based.

00:40:42.660 --> 00:40:45.331
But as you can see, look,
it's not black and white.

00:40:45.331 --> 00:40:46.330
It's not all or nothing.

00:40:46.330 --> 00:40:50.080
Any steps we can make
along that spectrum

00:40:50.080 --> 00:40:52.906
may accrue significant benefits.

00:40:52.906 --> 00:40:54.280
You can show this
experimentally.

00:40:54.280 --> 00:40:56.107
You take vegetarians,
you give them meat.

00:40:56.107 --> 00:40:57.690
What happens to their
blood pressures?

00:40:57.690 --> 00:40:59.630
They go up.

00:40:59.630 --> 00:41:02.000
Or you take some meat
eaters, remove meat,

00:41:02.000 --> 00:41:06.380
and the blood pressures
go down within seven days.

00:41:06.380 --> 00:41:08.770
And this is after the vast
majority already reduced

00:41:08.770 --> 00:41:13.370
their blood pressure medications
or eliminated them completely.

00:41:13.370 --> 00:41:15.354
They had to, otherwise
their blood pressures

00:41:15.354 --> 00:41:17.020
would bottom out
because you're actually

00:41:17.020 --> 00:41:19.139
treating the cause of
their blood pressure.

00:41:19.139 --> 00:41:20.930
And so you can't be on
blood pressure drugs

00:41:20.930 --> 00:41:22.690
if you have normal
blood pressure.

00:41:22.690 --> 00:41:25.150
Lower pressures on fewer drugs.

00:41:25.150 --> 00:41:29.140
That's the power of plants.

00:41:29.140 --> 00:41:30.940
So does the American
Heart Association

00:41:30.940 --> 00:41:32.780
recommend a no-meat diet?

00:41:32.780 --> 00:41:33.280
No.

00:41:33.280 --> 00:41:36.270
They recommend a low meat
diet, the so-called DASH diet.

00:41:36.270 --> 00:41:37.860
Why not vegetarian?

00:41:37.860 --> 00:41:40.060
When the DASH diet
was created, were they

00:41:40.060 --> 00:41:42.320
just not aware of
this landmark research

00:41:42.320 --> 00:41:45.510
done by Harvard's Frank Sacks?

00:41:45.510 --> 00:41:46.010
No.

00:41:46.010 --> 00:41:47.220
They were aware.

00:41:47.220 --> 00:41:50.020
The chair of the committee
that came up with the DASH diet

00:41:50.020 --> 00:41:53.605
was Frank Sacks.

00:41:53.605 --> 00:41:57.030
You see, the DASH diet
was explicitly designed.

00:41:57.030 --> 00:41:59.940
The number one goal of
capturing the blood pressure

00:41:59.940 --> 00:42:01.730
lowering benefits of
a vegetarian diet,

00:42:01.730 --> 00:42:05.660
yet contain enough
animal products

00:42:05.660 --> 00:42:08.510
to make them palatable
to the general public.

00:42:08.510 --> 00:42:12.810
They didn't think the public
could quite handle the truth.

00:42:12.810 --> 00:42:14.610
Now, but in their
defense you can

00:42:14.610 --> 00:42:16.050
see what they were thinking.

00:42:16.050 --> 00:42:21.480
I mean just like drugs never
work unless you actually

00:42:21.480 --> 00:42:24.702
take them, diets never work
unless you actually eat them.

00:42:24.702 --> 00:42:26.910
They're like, well, no one's
going to eat vegetarian.

00:42:26.910 --> 00:42:32.570
So maybe on a population scale,
if they kind of soft-pedal it,

00:42:32.570 --> 00:42:36.190
then we'd actually save
more lives overall.

00:42:36.190 --> 00:42:40.890
But tell that to the
thousand families a day

00:42:40.890 --> 00:42:44.630
that lose a loved one
to high blood pressure.

00:42:44.630 --> 00:42:51.230
Maybe it's time to start
telling Americans the truth.

00:42:51.230 --> 00:42:53.550
Killer number 14 is
Parkinson's disease.

00:42:53.550 --> 00:42:55.980
Does a plant-based diet reduce
the risk of Parkinson's?

00:42:55.980 --> 00:42:59.450
Well, most studies to date
suggest a link between dairy

00:42:59.450 --> 00:43:00.650
products and Parkinson's.

00:43:00.650 --> 00:43:01.670
But why?

00:43:01.670 --> 00:43:04.720
Well, there's evidence
that milk is contaminated

00:43:04.720 --> 00:43:06.240
with neurotoxic chemicals.

00:43:06.240 --> 00:43:08.510
High levels of pesticide
residues, for example,

00:43:08.510 --> 00:43:10.850
found in milk and in the
brains of Parkinson's victims.

00:43:10.850 --> 00:43:14.020
We're talking about pollutants
like tetrahydroisoquinoline

00:43:14.020 --> 00:43:15.940
here, which is actually
what scientists

00:43:15.940 --> 00:43:18.840
use to induce Parkinsonism
in primates in the lab.

00:43:18.840 --> 00:43:20.590
It's found mostly
in cheese actually.

00:43:20.590 --> 00:43:22.820
So maybe the dairy
industry should require

00:43:22.820 --> 00:43:24.550
toxin screenings of milk.

00:43:24.550 --> 00:43:26.340
Good luck with that.

00:43:26.340 --> 00:43:27.940
You can always
just not drink it.

00:43:27.940 --> 00:43:34.370
But then what would
happen to your bones?

00:43:34.370 --> 00:43:37.115
That's a marketing ploy,
if you look at the science.

00:43:37.115 --> 00:43:39.634
Milk does not appear to protect
against hip fracture risk,

00:43:39.634 --> 00:43:41.300
whether drinking
during your adult years

00:43:41.300 --> 00:43:42.966
or drinking milk
during your teen years.

00:43:42.966 --> 00:43:43.870
It doesn't matter.

00:43:43.870 --> 00:43:46.650
If anything, milk was
associated with an increase

00:43:46.650 --> 00:43:47.570
in fracture risk.

00:43:47.570 --> 00:43:50.140
Maybe that's why we
see higher hip fracture

00:43:50.140 --> 00:43:53.900
rates among the populations with
the greatest milk consumption.

00:43:53.900 --> 00:43:56.590
So Swedish researchers
decided to put it

00:43:56.590 --> 00:43:58.560
to the test, a hundred
thousand men and women

00:43:58.560 --> 00:43:59.790
followed for up to 20 years.

00:43:59.790 --> 00:44:04.470
And milk-drinking women
had higher rates of death.

00:44:04.470 --> 00:44:07.670
More heart disease,
significantly more cancer,

00:44:07.670 --> 00:44:10.150
associated with each daily
glass of milk consumption.

00:44:10.150 --> 00:44:17.600
Three glasses a day,
that's about a twofold risk

00:44:17.600 --> 00:44:21.200
of overall mortality, all-cause
mortality, risk of death.

00:44:21.200 --> 00:44:24.350
And they had significantly more
bone and hip fractures too,

00:44:24.350 --> 00:44:26.502
more milk, more fractures.

00:44:26.502 --> 00:44:29.800
Milk-drinking men also had
a higher risk of death.

00:44:29.800 --> 00:44:33.650
But for some reason, you
never see milk ads like this.

00:44:33.650 --> 00:44:36.090
I'm not sure why.

00:44:36.090 --> 00:44:37.869
Finally, aspiration
pneumonia, which

00:44:37.869 --> 00:44:40.160
is caused by swallowing
problems due to Parkinson's, or

00:44:40.160 --> 00:44:42.450
Alzheimer's, or stroke, things
that we've already covered.

00:44:42.450 --> 00:44:43.616
So where does this leave us?

00:44:43.616 --> 00:44:48.390
Here are the 15 leading
reasons Americans die.

00:44:48.390 --> 00:44:52.300
And a plant-based diet can help
prevent nearly all of them.

00:44:52.300 --> 00:44:54.890
Can help treat more
than half of them.

00:44:54.890 --> 00:44:57.930
In some cases, even
reverse the progression

00:44:57.930 --> 00:45:02.990
of disease in some cases,
including sometimes

00:45:02.990 --> 00:45:04.020
our top three killers.

00:45:04.020 --> 00:45:06.390
Now, look, there are
drugs that can help too.

00:45:06.390 --> 00:45:08.520
You take one drug,
cholesterol-lowering drugs,

00:45:08.520 --> 00:45:10.140
every day for the rest of your
life to help with your heart.

00:45:10.140 --> 00:45:12.010
Usually it takes
a couple families

00:45:12.010 --> 00:45:13.930
of blood pressure
lowering pills.

00:45:13.930 --> 00:45:17.620
Or you can insulin injections
to control your blood sugars.

00:45:17.620 --> 00:45:21.510
But the same diet,
though, does it all.

00:45:21.510 --> 00:45:24.050
So it's not like there's
one liver or a healthy diet.

00:45:24.050 --> 00:45:26.550
I know you want to go on the
heart healthy diet or the brain

00:45:26.550 --> 00:45:26.980
healthy diet.

00:45:26.980 --> 00:45:28.896
A liver healthy diet is
a kidney healthy diet,

00:45:28.896 --> 00:45:31.480
is a body healthy diet.

00:45:31.480 --> 00:45:34.966
One diet to rule them all.

00:45:34.966 --> 00:45:36.340
And what about
drug side effects?

00:45:36.340 --> 00:45:38.048
I'm not talking about
a little rash here.

00:45:38.048 --> 00:45:39.180
Side effects kill.

00:45:39.180 --> 00:45:42.492
Prescription drugs kill
more than a hundred

00:45:42.492 --> 00:45:45.680
thousand Americans every year.

00:45:45.680 --> 00:45:46.930
Wait a second.

00:45:46.930 --> 00:45:50.980
106,000 deaths a year from
adverse drug side effects.

00:45:50.980 --> 00:45:53.680
That means the sixth
leading cause of death

00:45:53.680 --> 00:45:56.170
is actually doctors.

00:45:56.170 --> 00:45:59.134
The sixth leading
cause of death is me.

00:45:59.134 --> 00:46:00.080
[LAUGHTER]

00:46:00.080 --> 00:46:03.810
Thankfully, I can be prevented
with a plan-based diet.

00:46:03.810 --> 00:46:04.620
No, seriously.

00:46:04.620 --> 00:46:05.745
I said drugs actually.

00:46:05.745 --> 00:46:09.600
A study, 15,000 American
vegetarians, compared to them,

00:46:09.600 --> 00:46:11.100
meat eaters had
about twice the odds

00:46:11.100 --> 00:46:14.194
of being on aspirin; sleeping
pills; tranquilizers; antacids;

00:46:14.194 --> 00:46:16.360
pain killers; blood pressure
medications; laxatives,

00:46:16.360 --> 00:46:18.620
of course; as well as insulin.

00:46:18.620 --> 00:46:20.820
So plant-based diets
are great for people

00:46:20.820 --> 00:46:22.590
that don't like taking
drugs, for those

00:46:22.590 --> 00:46:24.490
that don't like
paying for drugs,

00:46:24.490 --> 00:46:28.650
and don't like risking
drug side effects.

00:46:28.650 --> 00:46:31.620
Want to solve the
health care crisis?

00:46:31.620 --> 00:46:33.410
I've got a suggestion.

00:46:33.410 --> 00:46:35.250
There's only one
diet that's ever

00:46:35.250 --> 00:46:38.450
been proven to
reverse heart disease

00:46:38.450 --> 00:46:42.050
in a majority of patients,
a plant-based diet.

00:46:42.050 --> 00:46:44.410
So any time anyone
want to sell you

00:46:44.410 --> 00:46:47.310
on some new diet they
heard about, do me a favor,

00:46:47.310 --> 00:46:48.677
ask them this simple question.

00:46:48.677 --> 00:46:49.260
Wait a second.

00:46:49.260 --> 00:46:52.790
Has it been proven to reverse
heart disease, the number one

00:46:52.790 --> 00:46:54.790
reason me and all my
loved ones have died?

00:46:54.790 --> 00:46:58.870
If the answer is no, then why
would you even consider it?

00:46:58.870 --> 00:47:02.630
I mean if that's all a
plant-based diet could do,

00:47:02.630 --> 00:47:07.400
reverse our number one
killer, shouldn't that

00:47:07.400 --> 00:47:10.634
be like the default diet
until proven otherwise.

00:47:10.634 --> 00:47:12.050
And the fact that
it also would be

00:47:12.050 --> 00:47:14.020
helpful in preventing,
arresting, and reversing

00:47:14.020 --> 00:47:16.600
other leading killers, like type
2 diabetes and hypertension,

00:47:16.600 --> 00:47:20.270
would seem to make
the case overwhelming.

00:47:20.270 --> 00:47:24.460
Most deaths in the United States
are preventable and related

00:47:24.460 --> 00:47:25.926
to nutrition.

00:47:25.926 --> 00:47:27.550
According to the most
rigorous analysis

00:47:27.550 --> 00:47:29.780
of risk factors ever
published-- this is the Global

00:47:29.780 --> 00:47:32.279
Burden of Disease study funded
by the Bill and Melinda Gates

00:47:32.279 --> 00:47:33.657
Foundation-- the
number one cause

00:47:33.657 --> 00:47:35.740
of death in the United
States and number one cause

00:47:35.740 --> 00:47:38.710
of disability is our diet.

00:47:38.710 --> 00:47:42.642
And it has since bumped
tobacco smoking to number two.

00:47:42.642 --> 00:47:44.850
Smoking now only kills about
a half million Americans

00:47:44.850 --> 00:47:46.550
every year, whereas
our diet kills

00:47:46.550 --> 00:47:49.740
hundreds of thousands more.

00:47:49.740 --> 00:47:55.520
So let me end with a
thought experiment.

00:47:55.520 --> 00:48:02.160
Imagine yourself a
smoker back in the 1950s.

00:48:02.160 --> 00:48:05.810
The average per capita
consumption of cigarettes

00:48:05.810 --> 00:48:08.250
was about 4,000 a year.

00:48:08.250 --> 00:48:12.270
So the average American
smoked half a pack a day.

00:48:12.270 --> 00:48:14.810
Think about that.

00:48:14.810 --> 00:48:17.090
The media was
telling you to smoke.

00:48:17.090 --> 00:48:23.390
Famous athletes agreed, even
Santa Claus wanted you--

00:48:23.390 --> 00:48:30.012
I mean, look, you want to keep
fit and stay-- where are we--

00:48:30.012 --> 00:48:32.770
and stay slender.

00:48:32.770 --> 00:48:35.720
And so you make sure to smoke
and eat a lot of hot dogs

00:48:35.720 --> 00:48:36.920
to stay trim.

00:48:36.920 --> 00:48:40.120
And eat lots of the sugar
to stay slim and trim, a lot

00:48:40.120 --> 00:48:41.635
better than that apple there.

00:48:41.635 --> 00:48:42.260
I mean, sheesh.

00:48:45.460 --> 00:48:49.080
Though apples do connote
goodness and freshness,

00:48:49.080 --> 00:48:51.610
reads one internal
tobacco industry memo.

00:48:51.610 --> 00:48:53.110
Which brings up
many possibilities

00:48:53.110 --> 00:48:55.480
for making a
youth-oriented cigarette,

00:48:55.480 --> 00:48:57.360
like an apple-flavored
cigarette for kids.

00:48:57.360 --> 00:49:00.010
Ah, shameless.

00:49:00.010 --> 00:49:02.450
For digestion's sake, you smoke.

00:49:02.450 --> 00:49:05.060
I mean no curative power is
claimed by Philip Morris.

00:49:05.060 --> 00:49:07.650
But an ounce of prevention
is worth a pound of cure.

00:49:07.650 --> 00:49:13.330
So, hey, better safe
than sorry, and smoke.

00:49:13.330 --> 00:49:17.340
Blow in her face and
she'll follow you anywhere.

00:49:20.560 --> 00:49:22.100
No women ever says no.

00:49:22.100 --> 00:49:26.670
They're so round, so
firm, so fully packed.

