vegetable oil, like Crisco,

01:01:03.510 --> 01:01:04.340
like shortening.

01:01:04.340 --> 01:01:05.790
That's the worst
thing, transfats.

01:01:05.790 --> 01:01:07.081
It's worse than saturated fats.

01:01:07.081 --> 01:01:08.670
It's worse than processed meat.

01:01:08.670 --> 01:01:11.210
It's the worst thing
we can possibly eat.

01:01:11.210 --> 01:01:12.440
Its plant based technically.

01:01:12.440 --> 01:01:12.940
All right.

01:01:12.940 --> 01:01:16.075
So that's why I don't like
the term vegan, vegetarian.

01:01:16.075 --> 01:01:18.964
Because that tells me as a
physician what you don't eat.

01:01:18.964 --> 01:01:20.380
That doesn't tell
what you do eat.

01:01:20.380 --> 01:01:22.180
But that's why if
you tell me, well,

01:01:22.180 --> 01:01:24.430
I eat a whole food plant-based.

01:01:24.430 --> 01:01:24.930
OK.

01:01:24.930 --> 01:01:25.380
You tell me.

01:01:25.380 --> 01:01:25.690
OK.

01:01:25.690 --> 01:01:26.600
You're eating-- OK.

01:01:26.600 --> 01:01:28.190
But you can still screw that up.

01:01:28.190 --> 01:01:29.600
And how do you screw that up?

01:01:29.600 --> 01:01:32.590
By not ensuring a regular
reliable source of vitamin

01:01:32.590 --> 01:01:33.369
B-12.

01:01:33.369 --> 01:01:35.410
There's two vitamins that
are not made by plants.

01:01:35.410 --> 01:01:37.750
One is vitamin D, which
is made by animals,

01:01:37.750 --> 01:01:41.564
such as yourself, when you walk
outside and get some sunshine.

01:01:41.564 --> 01:01:42.730
It's actually not a vitamin.

01:01:42.730 --> 01:01:44.690
It's a hormone created by Sun.

01:01:44.690 --> 01:01:47.270
But no matter how
long you sunbathe

01:01:47.270 --> 01:01:50.610
naked in Times Square
on New Year's Day,

01:01:50.610 --> 01:01:52.850
the Sun's rays are at such
an angle at this latitude

01:01:52.850 --> 01:01:53.820
during the winter
months, you're not

01:01:53.820 --> 01:01:56.440
going to make any vitamin D.
January, February no vitamin D

01:01:56.440 --> 01:01:57.857
production in New York City.

01:01:57.857 --> 01:01:59.440
I mean they actually
did these studies

01:01:59.440 --> 01:02:02.110
using human foreskins
on the tops of buildings

01:02:02.110 --> 01:02:03.211
here in New York City.

01:02:03.211 --> 01:02:03.960
Because they were.

01:02:03.960 --> 01:02:05.220
You need human skin.

01:02:05.220 --> 01:02:06.410
Well, anyway.

01:02:06.410 --> 01:02:06.910
[LAUGHTER]

01:02:06.910 --> 01:02:08.782
No vitamin D
production whatsoever.

01:02:13.660 --> 01:02:17.010
So you need to get
vitamin D, depending

01:02:17.010 --> 01:02:19.230
on where you-- I mean we
evolved running around

01:02:19.230 --> 01:02:20.760
naked in equatorial
Africa, getting

01:02:20.760 --> 01:02:21.912
baked in the Sun all day.

01:02:21.912 --> 01:02:23.620
We're not used to
living at this latitude

01:02:23.620 --> 01:02:24.786
and wearing lots of clothes.

01:02:24.786 --> 01:02:25.540
OK.

01:02:25.540 --> 01:02:28.370
And vitamin B-12 is not
made by plants either,

01:02:28.370 --> 01:02:29.240
not made by animals.

01:02:29.240 --> 01:02:31.406
It's made by little microbes
that blanket the Earth.

01:02:31.406 --> 01:02:33.550
So we get all the B-12
we need drinking out

01:02:33.550 --> 01:02:35.170
of a mountain stream or
well water, or something.

01:02:35.170 --> 01:02:36.820
But now, we chlorinate
our water supply

01:02:36.820 --> 01:02:38.080
to kill off any bacteria.

01:02:38.080 --> 01:02:40.330
We just don't get a lot of
B-12 in our water any more.

01:02:40.330 --> 01:02:41.980
Don't get a lot
of cholera either.

01:02:41.980 --> 01:02:44.450
It's very good thing.

01:02:44.450 --> 01:02:47.280
But now, because we live in
such a sanitary situation.

01:02:47.280 --> 01:02:49.350
So our fellow
great apes get B-12

01:02:49.350 --> 01:02:51.130
from bugs, dirt, and feces.

01:02:51.130 --> 01:02:52.080
But, let's see.

01:02:52.080 --> 01:02:54.810
I prefer supplemental sources.

01:02:54.810 --> 01:02:56.820
So I recommend a
vitamin B-12 supplement

01:02:56.820 --> 01:03:00.260
people eating a plant-based
diet, one 2,500 microgram

01:03:00.260 --> 01:03:02.870
tablet once a week, costs
less than $3 a year,

01:03:02.870 --> 01:03:04.280
all the B-12 you need.

01:03:04.280 --> 01:03:05.780
There's also B-12
fortified foods,

01:03:05.780 --> 01:03:07.500
like there's soy milk,
and breakfast cereal,

01:03:07.500 --> 01:03:08.375
and things like that.

01:03:08.375 --> 01:03:11.400
But I encourage people to eat
less of those processed foods.

01:03:11.400 --> 01:03:13.670
So probably the safest,
cheapest way is just get it.

01:03:13.670 --> 01:03:15.170
But I'm so glad you
brought that up.

01:03:15.170 --> 01:03:17.370
Because that's critical.

01:03:17.370 --> 01:03:19.430
B-12 is critical for
neurological health

01:03:19.430 --> 01:03:20.650
and for blood health.

01:03:20.650 --> 01:03:21.904
AUDIENCE: What about omega-3?

01:03:21.904 --> 01:03:22.570
Is that a thing?

01:03:22.570 --> 01:03:23.950
MICHAEL GREGER: Oh, yeah.

01:03:23.950 --> 01:03:26.744
So there are essential fatty
acids-- omega-6 and omega-3

01:03:26.744 --> 01:03:27.660
essential fatty acids.

01:03:27.660 --> 01:03:29.243
Meaning that our
body can't make them.

01:03:29.243 --> 01:03:31.360
We need to take
them into our diet.

01:03:31.360 --> 01:03:33.070
And so the current
recommendations

01:03:33.070 --> 01:03:39.520
we need to get basically
about two grams of omega-3s.

01:03:39.520 --> 01:03:42.800
And so you can get that
in alpha-linolenic acid,

01:03:42.800 --> 01:03:44.610
like a tablespoon
of ground flaxseeds,

01:03:44.610 --> 01:03:46.620
all the omega-3s you'd
take for the day.

01:03:46.620 --> 01:03:48.487
So that's part of
my daily dozen foods

01:03:48.487 --> 01:03:50.570
I encourage people to eat
every day in their diet.

01:03:50.570 --> 01:03:52.200
Is that one of a
tablespoon of flaxseeds.

01:03:52.200 --> 01:03:52.700
Why?

01:03:52.700 --> 01:03:54.060
You need to get your omega-3s.

01:03:54.060 --> 01:03:56.290
Or you can also eat walnuts,
or dark-green leafy vegetables,

01:03:56.290 --> 01:03:57.960
or chia seeds, hemp
seeds, lots of things.

01:03:57.960 --> 01:03:59.668
But you need to get
those into your diet.

01:04:02.497 --> 01:04:04.580
And our bodies can take
those short-chain omega-3s

01:04:04.580 --> 01:04:07.020
and elongate them into
the so-called fish fats,

01:04:07.020 --> 01:04:08.390
like EPA and DHA.

01:04:08.390 --> 01:04:12.620
The question though is can we
do it enough for optimal health?

01:04:12.620 --> 01:04:15.450
And that I think still
remains an open question.

01:04:15.450 --> 01:04:19.550
So I actually encourage
people to take 250 milligrams

01:04:19.550 --> 01:04:23.210
of a pollutant-free, a source
of long-chain omega-3s, EPA

01:04:23.210 --> 01:04:24.327
or DHA.

01:04:24.327 --> 01:04:26.160
And the only way you
can do that gluten-free

01:04:26.160 --> 01:04:29.710
is either yeast-based or
algae-based EPA or DHA.

01:04:29.710 --> 01:04:32.210
That's actually where the fish
get it, from the first place.

01:04:32.210 --> 01:04:33.793
We can kind of cut
out the middle fish

01:04:33.793 --> 01:04:37.150
and go straight to the source.

01:04:37.150 --> 01:04:38.760
And not for heart
health, actually.

01:04:38.760 --> 01:04:40.630
Because the studies
have shown we now

01:04:40.630 --> 01:04:43.595
know that recommendations to
increase fatty fish consumption

01:04:43.595 --> 01:04:45.220
and take fish oil
capsules don't appear

01:04:45.220 --> 01:04:49.130
to help prevent heart disease
or help treat heart disease--

01:04:49.130 --> 01:04:51.930
but for cognitive health.

01:04:51.930 --> 01:04:57.430
There's this study linking kind
of accelerated cerebral volume

01:04:57.430 --> 01:05:02.651
loss with low
omega-3 index, which

01:05:02.651 --> 01:05:03.900
are these long-chain omega-3s.

01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:07.960
So I encourage people to
include that, absolutely.

01:05:07.960 --> 01:05:09.070
Great, a good question.

01:05:09.070 --> 01:05:10.387
Thank you.

