have whole grain pasta.

01:06:52.390 --> 01:06:53.930
And actually sweet
potatoes, I think

01:06:53.930 --> 01:06:55.346
are healthier than
white potatoes.

01:06:55.346 --> 01:06:58.230
And I give my kind
of reasons why.

01:06:58.230 --> 01:07:02.850
And in general, flour products,
even when they're whole wheat,

01:07:02.850 --> 01:07:03.810
are not great.

01:07:03.810 --> 01:07:08.200
Because you actually you
starve your microbial self.

01:07:10.775 --> 01:07:13.150
So they do these really neat
studies where they basically

01:07:13.150 --> 01:07:14.620
give people the same diet.

01:07:14.620 --> 01:07:16.820
But they grind up
everything beforehand.

01:07:16.820 --> 01:07:19.680
So instead of beans, they
give some people chick peas,

01:07:19.680 --> 01:07:20.550
some people humus.

01:07:20.550 --> 01:07:23.430
They give some people bread
and some people like actually

01:07:23.430 --> 01:07:24.650
wheat berries.

01:07:24.650 --> 01:07:25.880
And you do that for grains.

01:07:25.880 --> 01:07:28.800
And you chop up your oatmeal
or steel-cut oatmeal.

01:07:28.800 --> 01:07:33.330
And you can dramatically boost
the weight of their stool.

01:07:33.330 --> 01:07:35.790
And actually most of
the weight of a stool

01:07:35.790 --> 01:07:37.150
is actually pure bacteria.

01:07:37.150 --> 01:07:40.160
It's just trillions and
trillions of bacteria.

01:07:40.160 --> 01:07:42.860
There's so much food
because little pieces

01:07:42.860 --> 01:07:44.310
of starch-- and
starch, no matter

01:07:44.310 --> 01:07:46.586
how well you chew,
actually get down or past

01:07:46.586 --> 01:07:48.460
our small intestine into
our lower intestine.

01:07:48.460 --> 01:07:50.834
And these are the prebiotics,
the fiber-resistant starch.

01:07:50.834 --> 01:07:53.300
The prebiotics that feed our
good gut bacteria, so much

01:07:53.300 --> 01:07:56.490
so that they go
crazy when you eat

01:07:56.490 --> 01:08:00.620
kind of whole intact grains,
not just whole grains.

01:08:00.620 --> 01:08:03.220
So whole intact grains are
preferable because then we

01:08:03.220 --> 01:08:04.630
leave some for our gut bacteria.

01:08:04.630 --> 01:08:06.755
And we're learning more
and more about the benefits

01:08:06.755 --> 01:08:07.780
of the microbiome.

01:08:07.780 --> 01:08:11.940
Whereas when you process foods
into flour or grind them up,

01:08:11.940 --> 01:08:15.610
they become so efficiently
absorbed that other

01:08:15.610 --> 01:08:17.979
than the fiber, you're
not leaving anything.

01:08:17.979 --> 01:08:18.920
And we feed them.

01:08:18.920 --> 01:08:19.560
They feed us.

01:08:19.560 --> 01:08:22.670
There's really some cool stuff
out there about the microbiome.

01:08:22.670 --> 01:08:23.670
Yes?

