And so like do some of those
pieces sort of end cancelling

01:15:57.010 --> 01:15:57.510
out?

01:15:57.510 --> 01:15:57.820
MICHAEL GREGER: Hm.

01:15:57.820 --> 01:15:58.230
OK.

01:15:58.230 --> 01:15:58.580
Yeah, yeah.

01:15:58.580 --> 01:15:59.200
No.

01:15:59.200 --> 01:15:59.550
Yeah.

01:15:59.550 --> 01:16:01.841
There's been some interesting
kind of computer modeling

01:16:01.841 --> 01:16:02.410
studies.

01:16:02.410 --> 01:16:05.860
So there's one famous one of
food and chemical toxicology

01:16:05.860 --> 01:16:08.620
that suggested that
if half of Americans

01:16:08.620 --> 01:16:11.050
ate a single more serving
of fruits and vegetables,

01:16:11.050 --> 01:16:15.990
then we would prevent every
year 20,000 cancer deaths,

01:16:15.990 --> 01:16:18.180
not just cancer cases,
20,000 cancer deaths.

01:16:18.180 --> 01:16:21.639
People that would have died had
it not been for half of America

01:16:21.639 --> 01:16:23.930
eating more and more servings
of fruits and vegetables.

01:16:23.930 --> 01:16:25.846
That's how powerful
fruits and vegetables are.

01:16:25.846 --> 01:16:28.530
But because they were
modeling conventional fruits

01:16:28.530 --> 01:16:30.880
and vegetables, that
additional pesticide

01:16:30.880 --> 01:16:33.210
load from all that
extra conventional fruit

01:16:33.210 --> 01:16:36.420
and vegetable consumption, would
cause, in their estimation,

01:16:36.420 --> 01:16:38.290
10 cancer deaths.

01:16:38.290 --> 01:16:42.480
So you only end up
preventing 19,990 cancers.

01:16:42.480 --> 01:16:45.100
So you get this tremendous
benefit and then

01:16:45.100 --> 01:16:46.300
a small bump in risk.

01:16:46.300 --> 01:16:46.930
That's true.

01:16:46.930 --> 01:16:48.230
Why accept any risk at all?

01:16:48.230 --> 01:16:49.900
Choose organic, great.

01:16:49.900 --> 01:16:52.150
But we should never let
concern about pesticides

01:16:52.150 --> 01:16:54.960
prevent us from stuffing
our face with as many fruits

01:16:54.960 --> 01:16:57.426
and vegetables as possible.

01:16:57.426 --> 01:16:59.000
AUDIENCE: And what
about the oil too?

01:16:59.000 --> 01:16:59.970
MICHAEL GREGER: Oh, yeah.

01:16:59.970 --> 01:17:01.240
So if you're going
