01:18:13.611 --> 01:18:15.084
AUDIENCE: So a
lot of vegetarians

01:18:15.084 --> 01:18:17.063
will look to things
like shakes or powders

01:18:17.063 --> 01:18:18.521
to supplement their
protein intake.

01:18:18.521 --> 01:18:20.604
Have they been any studies
on whey protein isolate

01:18:20.604 --> 01:18:22.940
and if [INAUDIBLE] the
same immune inflammation

01:18:22.940 --> 01:18:25.494
response as dairy, like a glass
of milk, a piece of cheese?

01:18:25.494 --> 01:18:26.410
MICHAEL GREGER: Right.

01:18:26.410 --> 01:18:27.130
Yeah.

01:18:27.130 --> 01:18:29.965
So whey, the biggest
problem with whey proteins

01:18:29.965 --> 01:18:31.470
is their high leucine content.

01:18:31.470 --> 01:18:34.090
So leucine is a branched
chain amino acid

01:18:34.090 --> 01:18:37.920
that activates this kind of
engine of aging enzyme called

01:18:37.920 --> 01:18:40.180
mTOR, which is a
fascinating story.

01:18:40.180 --> 01:18:41.680
I've got a bunch
of videos about it.

01:18:41.680 --> 01:18:44.780
It's just this really
neat detective story.

01:18:44.780 --> 01:18:48.919
I mean milk has
evolved to do what?

01:18:48.919 --> 01:18:49.960
To promote growth, right.

01:18:49.960 --> 01:18:52.540
So dairy milk, literally
to put a couple pounds

01:18:52.540 --> 01:18:54.120
on a calf in a matter of months.

01:18:54.120 --> 01:18:56.510
And so it's supremely
designed to both boost

01:18:56.510 --> 01:18:59.050
IGF-1, boost mTOR signaling.

01:18:59.050 --> 01:19:01.350
Boost can accelerate growth.

01:19:01.350 --> 01:19:05.220
Which is not so great if you've
already reached adult height.

01:19:05.220 --> 01:19:07.580
So accelerating growth,
so having growth hormones

01:19:07.580 --> 01:19:10.210
and growth factors in your body
at this stage, not so great.

01:19:10.210 --> 01:19:13.221
Because many of us are actually
harboring so-called occult

01:19:13.221 --> 01:19:13.720
tumors.

01:19:16.900 --> 01:19:19.990
So even women by their
40s-- they actually

01:19:19.990 --> 01:19:21.930
do autopsies studies,
if you get hit by a bus.

01:19:21.930 --> 01:19:23.570
They have microscopic
breast tumors.

01:19:23.570 --> 01:19:26.720
Most men actually have
microscopic prostate tumors.

01:19:26.720 --> 01:19:28.450
So, for example,
American men have

01:19:28.450 --> 01:19:31.970
the same rates of prostate
cancer as Japanese men,

01:19:31.970 --> 01:19:34.500
but a tiny fraction of the
death from prostate cancer.

01:19:34.500 --> 01:19:36.750
They die with their tumors,
instead from their tumors,

01:19:36.750 --> 01:19:40.540
because there's a
third stage of cancer.

01:19:40.540 --> 01:19:44.420
There's cancer initiation,
the first mutated DNA

01:19:44.420 --> 01:19:45.676
that creates the cancer cell.

01:19:45.676 --> 01:19:47.800
And then there's a promotion
stage, where it grows.

01:19:47.800 --> 01:19:49.220
It can grow for decades.

01:19:49.220 --> 01:19:51.490
Epithelial tumors,
like colon cancer,

01:19:51.490 --> 01:19:54.671
prostate cancer, breast cancer,
can take decades to grow.

01:19:54.671 --> 01:19:56.670
And then the progression
stage, where it kind of

01:19:56.670 --> 01:19:57.670
spreads around the body.

01:19:57.670 --> 01:20:02.840
But in that stage, I mean it
takes a billion cancer cells

01:20:02.840 --> 01:20:04.960
to show up on a mammography.

01:20:04.960 --> 01:20:07.000
So early detection
with mammography

01:20:07.000 --> 01:20:10.050
is really, really
late detection.

01:20:10.050 --> 01:20:12.640
And so it's all about
slowing the doubling time.

01:20:12.640 --> 01:20:15.340
So breast cancer cells
take between a few weeks

01:20:15.340 --> 01:20:18.080
to a few months to
double once in size.

01:20:18.080 --> 01:20:21.310
But we love the mathematics
of exponential growth.

01:20:21.310 --> 01:20:25.560
If you double 30 times, and
boom, we got a billion cells.

01:20:25.560 --> 01:20:28.250
But you don't care if
you get breast cancer

01:20:28.250 --> 01:20:29.330
in a century from now.

01:20:29.330 --> 01:20:31.060
You don't expect to
be around that long.

01:20:31.060 --> 01:20:32.800
So it's not just about
preventing cancer,

01:20:32.800 --> 01:20:34.640
but slowing down the
growth of cancer.

01:20:37.194 --> 01:20:39.110
And so the reason we
think that high the IGF-1

01:20:39.110 --> 01:20:41.440
levels, and high mTOR
signaling, and leucine intake

01:20:41.440 --> 01:20:43.820
is associated with
these cancers is

01:20:43.820 --> 01:20:47.590
because-- it's not that
they're causing the cancer.

01:20:47.590 --> 01:20:50.500
But they're kind of amplifying
the growth of whatever

01:20:50.500 --> 01:20:51.840
hidden tumors you have.

01:20:51.840 --> 01:20:55.080
And so they actually appear
within your lifespan,

01:20:55.080 --> 01:20:59.080
which is something that we
don't want to have happen.

